-- Russian cenbank moves to limit pricing manipulation in futures market 
-- 
-- Mon Dec 15, 2014 08:16AM EST
-- None



MOSCOW, Dec 15 (Reuters) - The Russian central bank said on Monday it had sent an order to the Moscow Exchange <MOEX.MM> to halt trading in certain instruments in order to prevent possible manipulation of the equity futures market.

"In order to prevent possible pricing manipulation during the expiration of futures contracts on the RTS index <.IRTS> .... the Central Bank of Russia sent an order to MICEX <.MCX> (index) to suspend trading of financial instruments," the bank said in a statement. The dollar-based RTS and the rouble-traded MICEX are part of the Moscow Exchange.